prioritized%20except%20family%20and%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOutset%20is%20backed%20by%20Y%20Combinator%20and%20raised%20%2430%20million%20in%20Series%20B%20funding%20in%20December.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Aaron%20Cannon%2C%20the%2037-year-old%20founder%20of%20Outset%2C%20who%20resides%20in%20San%20Francisco%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20three-year-old%20son.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20start%20my%20company%20while%20I%20was%20on%20paternity%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20very%20woven%20together%3A%20starting%20a%20family%20and%20starting%20a%20startup%20happened%20along%20a%20similar%20timeline.%20I%20definitely%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20think%20that's%20a%20little%20insane.%20It%20is.%20I%20have%20wistful%20moments%20thinking%20about%2C%20%26quot%3BMan%2C%20what%20if%20I%20could%20do%20all%20this%20when%20I%20was%2025%20and%20single%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20quickly%20remind%20myself%20that%20I%20was%20an%20idiot%20when%20I%20was%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20on%20paternity%20leave%2C%20I%20maybe%20had%20too%20much%20time%20to%20think.%20When%20you%20have%20a%20baby%2C%20you%20are%20all%20hands%20on%20deck%20physically%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20intellectual%20stimulation.%20I%20was%20daydreaming%20about%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20very%20intense%20balance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-advice-i-ever-got-about-work-life-balance-came-from-partners-mom-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BWork-life%20balance%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20implies%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20chillness.%20I%20don't%20have%20that.%20Every%20minute%20of%20my%20day%20matters.%20Everything%20gets%20deprioritized%20except%20family%20and%20work.%20That's%20painful.%20It's%20really%20ruthless%20prioritization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20very%20weird%20mentally.%20In%20a%20normal%20job%2C%20you%20have%20really%20intense%20days%2C%20and%20you%20come%20home%20and%20you%20tell%20your%20family%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20got%20to%20take%20a%20breather.%26quot%3B%20The%20problem%20is%2C%20every%20day%20at%20my%20job%20right%20now%20is%20intense.%20Our%20startup%20is%20in%20that%20crazy%20growth%20stage%20where%20everything%20is%20growing%20and%20breaking%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20come%20home%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BUgh%2C%20this%20is%20so%20intense%2C%26quot%3B%20then%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20be%20as%20present%20as%20a%20dad.%20I%20don't%20have%20that%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesterday%2C%20on%20the%20way%20home%2C%20I%20had%20an%20intense%20call%20after%20work.%20I'm%20negotiating%20this%20contract.%20Then%20I%20pick%20up%20my%20kid%2C%20and%20I%20spend%20the%20next%2020%20minutes%20explaining%20seasons%20to%20him.%20I%20started%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20understand%20what%20a%20year%20is%3F%26quot%3B%20No.%20Where%20do%20you%20even%20start%3F%20It's%20a%20crazy%20mental%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20pick%20him%20up%20every%20day%2C%20which%20forces%20a%20boundary.%20Thank%20goodness%2C%20my%20cofounder%20and%20I%20have%20different%20lives.%20He%20stays%20later%2C%20I%20come%20earlier.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20two%20of%20us%20are%20showing%20up%20in%20the%20way%20the%20founders%20need%20to%2C%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20leave.%20I%20go%20and%20pick%20up%20my%20kid%20every%20day%20from%20preschool.%20I%20take%20him%20home.%20I%20do%20dinner.%20I%20get%20him%20to%20bed.%20Then%20I'm%20back%20on%20for%20work.%20Those%20are%20a%20precious%20couple%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20I'm%20physically%20present%2C%20it%20is%20very%20hard%20after%20the%20most%20intense%20day%20of%20work%20to%20just%20shut%20that%20off.%20You%20can%20set%20physical%20world%20boundaries%20and%20still%20be%20mentally%20there%20or%20not%20there.%20I%20want%20to%20be%20as%20deeply%20engaged%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-doge-startups-government-waste-ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EY%20Combinator%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20in%202023%2C%20and%20I%20was%20definitely%20on%20the%20older%20side.%20On%20Wednesday%20nights%2C%20we%20had%20speakers%20and%20programs%2C%20and%20that%20was%20not%20easy%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20dad%20provides%20perspective.%20It%20is%20easy%20to%20take%20any%20big%20thing%20or%20small%20thing%20that's%20happening%20and%20obsess%20as%20a%20founder.%20You%20are%20the%20company%2C%20the%20company%20is%20you.%20When%20I%20get%20home%20and%20have%20to%20explain%20what%20seasons%20are%2C%20it's%20a%20reminder%3A%20Why%20are%20we%20doing%20this%3F%20It%20zooms%20you%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20helps%20reinforce%20my%20motivations.%20I%20want%20my%20kid%20growing%20up%2C%20seeing%20his%20dad%20do%20a%20big%20swing%20in%20his%20career%20and%20try%20something%20crazy.%20That's%20a%20lesson%20and%20an%20example%20I%20want%20to%20set%20for%20him.%20You%20can%20go%20build%20something%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20chapter%20of%20my%20life%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20all%20of%20my%20life.%20It's%20intense.%20I%20should%20expect%20it%20to%20be%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20that%20I'm%20present%20as%20a%20dad.%20I%20don't%20get%20these%20years%20back.%20He's%20only%20three%20for%20one%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-founder-balance-work-being-dad-parenting-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1766692325000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693b11d064858d02d216a777%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-founder-balance-