2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20the%20unretirement%20rate%20from%20pre-COVID%20through%20mid-2024%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marketwatch.com%2Fstory%2Fwhen-retirees-go-back-to-work-is-it-a-sign-of-a-strong-labor-force-or-a-recession-779d295c%3Fgaa_at%3Deafs%26gaa_n%3DAWEtsqeZeWDj1LJEb2rFSwtWwcUlpZNynnMv3duvtXzL0JP6hSi1xoK_noHnVo2G7fY%253D%26gaa_ts%3D694d543a%26gaa_sig%3DQ4WpzzSSpUbjt_nmsj6t10MNDzj7JUtN40kcHtpryJO4-wjzKmvDQOmZ50WjCpYIRYxnk3Ebgo5o-dF9Fq3Udg%253D%253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esteadily%20declined%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%203.2%25%20in%20late%202018%20to%201.9%25%2C%20which%20suggests%20older%20workers%20are%20struggling%20to%20rejoin%20the%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F80-over-80-watch-video-read-all-stories-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E80%20Over%2080%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%2C%20which%20explored%20why%20people%20continue%20to%20work%20into%20their%2080s%20and%2090s%2C%20found%20that%204.2%25%20of%20Americans%2080%20and%20older%20work%2C%20the%20highest%20it's%20been%20in%20decades.%20Many%20unretired%20after%20months%2C%20years%2C%20or%20decades%20of%20not%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20recent%20surveys%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20from%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20show%20that%20retirement%20is%20elongating%20as%20life%20spans%20grow%20%E2%80%94%20and%20may%20be%20harder%20to%20achieve%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20the%20rise%20in%20costs%2C%20people's%20fixed%20incomes%2C%20their%20Social%20Security%20benefits%2C%20aren't%20enough%20to%20cover%20all%20their%20expenses%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sen.%20Kirsten%20Gillibrand%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20New%20York%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%2047%25%20of%20workers%20lack%20access%20to%20employer-sponsored%20retirement%20plans%2C%20and%2055%25%20report%20no%20dedicated%20retirement%20savings.%20We%20know%20that%20many%20seniors%20won't%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20retire%20comfortably.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22260f2545-db28-457a-b716-6a9c45c654be%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmericans%20want%20to%20retire%2C%20but%20actually%20doing%20so%20is%20a%20different%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESurveys%20published%20this%20year%20continue%20to%20show%20that%20Americans%20prioritize%20a%20healthy%20and%20stable%20retirement.%20However%2C%20many%20aren't%20taking%20the%20necessary%20steps%20to%20get%20there%2C%20and%20many%20aren't%20in%20financial%20or%20employment%20situations%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Bank%20report%20found%20that%2037%25%20of%20working%20adults%20are%20actively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-regrets-lessons-advice-boomers-gen-z-career-savings-work-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epreparing%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%2048%25%20of%20Americans%20contribute%20to%20their%20retirement%20savings.%20Nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20Generation%20X%20respondents%20said%20they%20have%20abandoned%20their%20goal%20of%20retiring.%20Three-quarters%20of%20millennials%20and%20Generation%20Z%20worried%20about%20needing%20to%20come%20out%20of%20retirement%2C%20as%20many%20of%20the%20traditional%20milestones%20%E2%80%94%20buying%20a%20house%20or%20starting%20a%20family%20%E2%80%94%20feel%20harder%20to%20grasp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20hasn't%20done%20many%20favors%20for%20older%20Americans%2C%20either.%20The%20Resume%20Builder%20survey%20found%20that%2054%25%20of%20older%20Americans%20who%20still%20work%20or%20are%20unretiring%20cited%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20while%20a%20similar%20amount%20said%20they%20enjoyed%20work.%20Inflation%20has%20remained%20stubbornly%20high%20this%20year%2C%20registering%20at%202.7%25%20for%20the%2012%20months%20ending%20in%20November.%20Inflation%20has%20been%20higher%20than%20the%20overall%20average%20for%20housing%20and%20various%20medical%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20further%20found%20that%20over%20a%20quarter%20of%20older%20workers%20were%20nervous%20about%20potential%20Social%20Security%20changes%2C%20while%20a%20fifth%20were%20concerned%20about%20Medicare%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20many%20seniors%2C%20retirement%20has%20become%20more%20flexible%20than%20final%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FResumeBuilder.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResumeBuilder.com%3C%2Fa%3E's%20chief%20career%20advisor%20Stacie%20Haller%20in%20the%20survey%20release.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20today's%20workplace%20offers%20far%20more%20flexible%20opportunities%20for%20older%20professionals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFaced%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-find-work-employment-hiring-slowdown-careers-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edifficult%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%2C%20many%20older%20Americans%20said%20they%20won't%20relinquish%20their%20job%20because%20they%20anticipate%20not%20being%20able%20to%20find%20another%2C%20citing%20factors%20such%20as%20ageism.%20The%20AARP%20Research%20survey%20found%20that%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20older%20workers%20believe%20it%20would%20be%20challenging%20for%20them%20to%20find%20another%20job%2C%20especially%20since%20older%20workers%20already%20experience%20longer%20stretches%20of%20unemployment%20on%20average%20than%20younger%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20who%20unretired%20said%20they've%20opted%20for%20part-time%20employment%20or%20gig%20work%2C%20which%20were%20easier%20to%20secure%20and%20maintain.%20A%20few%20returned%20to%20school%20or%20took%20online%20classes%20to%20improve%20their%20skills%20in%20hopes%20of%20finding%20more%20stable%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20many%20of%20those%20still%20working%20into%20their%2070s%2C%2080s%2C%20and%2090s%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-cant-retire-working-at-87-aging-low-wage-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewouldn't%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20if%20they%20had%20the%20means%20to.%20However%2C%20dozens%20said%20they%20wished%20they%20could%20work%20fewer%20hours%2C%20more%20flexible%20hours%2C%20or%20in%20a%20different%20profession%20that%20didn't%20wear%20them%20down%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a219b18-84bd-48f0-9dbe-218ecac7b89c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'No%20shame'%20in%20returning%20to%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20year%2C%20experts%20on%20retirement%20and%20aging%20stressed%20that%20returning%20to%20work%20was%20not%20something%20to%20view%20as%20shameful.%20Research%20papers%20overwhelmingly%20show%20the%20benefits%20of%20continuing%20to%20work%20in%20one's%20later%20years%2C%20such%20as%20sustained%20cognitive%20function%20and%20improved%20mental%20health%20outcomes%20%E2%80%94%20provided%20the%20worker%20has%20flexibility%20and%20can%20handle%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20insights%20seemed%20to%20put%20some%20older%20readers%20at%20ease.%20In%20interviews%2C%20dozens%20of%20workers%20in%20their%2080s%20said%20they%20felt%20like%20a%20failure%20for%20not%20being%20in%20a%20position%20to%20retire%20or%20pass%20down%20a%20significant%20inheritance%20to%20their%20children%2C%20though%20hearing%20that%20they%20weren't%20alone%20made%20them%20feel%20more%20confident.%20In%20responses%20and%20emails%20to%20my%20articles%2C%20some%20older%20readers%20said%20they%20considered%20going%20back%20to%20work%20after%20reading%20about%20many%20people%20who%20successfully%20did%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20politicians%2C%20researchers%20on%20aging%2C%20and%20anti-ageism%20advocates%20said%20more%20should%20be%20done%20in%20the%20short%20term%20to%20ensure%20older%20Americans%20have%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fageism-workplace-older-workers-job-search-hiring-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployment%20opportunities%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20need%20to%20live%20comfortably%20and%20have%20more%20financial%20support%20to%20guide%20them%20through%20their%20later%20years.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20some%20experts%20said%20that%20returning%20to%20work%20shouldn't%20be%20the%20long-term%20solution%2C%20as%20the%20safety%20net%20should%20be%20more%20robust%20so%20people%20only%20need%20to%20return%20to%20work%20if%20they%20desire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20our%20older%20adults%20need%20resources%20to%20survive%2C%20and%20so%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20workforce%20is%20available%20to%20them%2C%20and%20they%20won't%20be%20discriminated%20against%20from%20being%20hired%20and%20working%20if%20they%20need%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Gillibrand%20said%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20Protecting%20Older%20Americans%20Act%20she%20co-introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funretiring-older-workers-retirement-social-security-aging-part-time-employment-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1766687887000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694d8179832e0ef1ead6d21f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funretiring-older-workers-retirement-social-security-aging-part-time-employment-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20older%20Americans%20are%20returning%20to%20work%20due%20to%20financial%20insecurity%20and%20rising%20costs%2C%20as%20surveys%20show%20retirees%20fear%20their%20savings%20won't%20last%2C%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40businessinsider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funretiring-older-workers-retirement-social-security-aging-part-time-employment-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2