n%20after%20winning%20the%201949%20British%20Open.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EReisman%20discovered%20his%20talent%20for%20playing%20ping-pong%20at%20a%20young%20age%20in%20New%20York%20City's%20Lower%20East%20Side%20and%20became%20a%20junior%20champion%20when%20he%20was%2013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicknamed%20%26quot%3BThe%20Needle%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20his%20thin%20fame%2C%20Reisman%20was%20described%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20250622001350%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fvault.si.com%2Fvault%2F1977%2F11%2F21%2Fa-little-night-music%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1977%20Sports%20Illustrated%20profile%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20James%20Bond%20of%20table%20tennis%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20his%20creative%20shots%20and%20charismatic%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20won%2022%20titles%20over%20his%20career%2C%20which%20spanned%20the%20late%201940s%20to%202002.%20He%20won%20five%20bronze%20medals%20at%20the%20World%20Table%20Tennis%20Championships%20in%20that%20time%2C%20as%20well%20as%20two%20United%20States%20Open%20titles%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DEGLkkd_r9D4%26t%3D104s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBritish%20Open%20crown%20at%20London's%20Wembley%20Stadium%20in%201949%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20featured%20him%20doing%20a%20shot%20between%20his%20legs%20and%20forehand%20shots%20clocked%20at%20115%20mph%2C%20which%20the%20British%20press%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Atomic%20Blast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20wasn't%20playing%20competitively%2C%20Reisman%20traveled%20with%20the%20Harlem%20Globetrotters%2C%20entertaining%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20with%20trick-filled%20performances%20all%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201970s%2C%20he%20ran%20the%20Riverside%20Table%20Tennis%20Club%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20which%20became%20the%20hot%20spot%20for%20top%20players%2C%20as%20well%20as%20celebrities%20who%20loved%20to%20play%20table%20tennis%2C%20like%20Dustin%20Hoffman%20and%20Walter%20Matthau.%20Even%20chess%20sensation%20Bobby%20Fischer%20could%20be%20spotted%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e2082ca-8a58-4ef6-acd2-2993e43310cd%5C%22%3EFrom%20hawking%20watches%20to%20smuggling%20gold%20bars%2C%20Reisman%20always%20had%20side%20hustles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Timothee%20Chalamet%20running%20through%20the%20streets%20of%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6944410a04eda4732f2dcba8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221716%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETimoth%C3%A9e%20Chalamet%20in%20%26quot%3BMarty%20Supreme.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EA24%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EReisman%20was%20known%20for%20hustling%2C%20and%20was%20always%20devising%20ways%20to%20make%20a%20quick%20buck%20while%20traveling%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sports%20Illustrated%20story%20highlighted%20his%20antics%2C%20which%20included%20him%20coming%20home%20from%20his%20first%20trip%20to%20London%20with%20a%20bag%20full%20of%20nylon%20stockings%2C%20which%20he%20sold%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20New%20York%20for%20five%20times%20what%20he%20paid%20for%20them.%20During%20trips%20to%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20he%20smuggled%20gold%20bars%20out%20of%20the%20country%2C%20earning%20%241%2C000%20each%20time%20(he%20boasted%20in%20the%20story%20that%20he%20did%20it%2025%20times).%20When%20he%20finally%20stopped%20jet-setting%20and%20returned%20to%20NYC%20for%20good%20in%20the%20late%201950s%2C%20he%20went%20through%20customs%20with%20two%20dozen%20Rolex%20watches%20hidden%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20greatest%20scheme%20was%20the%20way%20he%20sought%20revenge%20on%20his%20nemesis%2C%20Japanese%20player%20Hiroji%20Satoh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%201952%20world%20championships%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Satoh%2C%20using%20a%20new%20paddle%20featuring%20foam%20rubber%2C%20blew%20through%20the%20competition%2C%20including%20Reisman.%20It%20was%20a%20landmark%20moment%2C%20as%20the%20paddle%20has%20since%20become%20the%20standard%20in%20the%20sport.%20But%20Reisman%20would%20not%20go%20quietly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReisman%20and%20Doug%20Cartland%2C%20who%20was%20his%20partner%20during%20the%20Globetrotter%20events%2C%20worked%20their%20way%20from%20Bombay%20through%20the%20Far%20East%20hustling%20and%20doing%20exhibitions%2C%20and%20eventually%20made%20it%20to%20Tokyo.%20There%2C%20the%20duo%20publicly%20challenged%20Satoh%20and%20Nobi%20Hayashi%2C%20a%20world%20doubles%20champion%2C%20to%20a%20match.%20The%20event%20was%20held%20on%20the%20stage%20of%20a%20movie%20theater%20in%20Osaka.%20Fans%20who%20couldn't%20fit%20in%20the%205%2C000-seat%20venue%20could%20hear%20the%20happenings%20on%20national%20radio%2C%20which%20covered%20the%20US%20vs.%20Japan%20showdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20event%20came%20down%20to%20a%20singles%20match%20between%20Reisman%20and%20Satoh.%20Reisman%20won%2C%20causing%20such%20an%20embarrassment%20for%20Satoh%20that%20he%20never%20played%20international%20competition%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22518b3c7c-3c19-40d5-b9f2-28e91db05f1e%5C%22%3EReisman%20was%20a%20master%20of%20trick%20shots%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marty%20Reisman%20doing%20a%20trick%20show%20with%20handle%20of%20paddle%20hitting%20the%20ping%20pong%20ball%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6944440604eda4732f2dcc18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222461%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarty%20Reisman%20hitting%20the%20ping%20pong%20with%20the%20handle%20of%20his%20paddle.%3Cp%3EJacobsen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20movie%2C%20Chalamet's%20Mauser%20possesses%20incredible%20talent%20for%20ping-pong%20and%20a%20penchant%20for%20trick%20shots.%20This%20seems%20to%20be%20heavily%20influenced%20by%20Reisman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReisman%20wo